<seg id=1> Students Back to High and Elementary Schools in Disaster Area of Zhejiang Province </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Hangzhou, September 2 (by Journalist Shen Haixiong and Shen Xiquan) - The educational circle in Zhejiang disaster area suffered a lot because of typhoon No.17. 1,500 schools had their premises, and facilities damaged. </seg>
<seg id=3> With the government and people's great effort of fighting against calamity and regeneration through their own endeavor, most high and elementary schools in disaster areas have now reverted to normal classes. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Recently, the educational departments of Zhejiang province have sent working groups to Wenzhou and Taizhou etc to guide the restoring work of education in disaster areas. </seg>
<seg id=5> The education committee of Wenzhou city mobilized more than 20 office cadres, who were divided into 7 groups, to Leqing, Ouhai, Dongtou, and Pingyang etc to assist the repairing of school and preparation for class, and also squeezed out 200,000 yuan from the educational funds for the special purpose of education and disaster relief. </seg>
<seg id=6> In order to ensure that students could go to school in time, the educational services in counties, cities, and regions of disaster area reduced the tuition fee or afforded some subsidies to those students whose families were suffered from economic difficulties due to this disaster. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> The school leaders and staffs in disaster areas went to work voluntarily ahead of schedule, earnestly cleaned the campus environment and put everything in order, took health measures and did disinfections, and repaired the damaged premises. </seg>
<seg id=8> Educational committee and Communist Youth league committee of Wenzhou combined with teachers and students in disaster areas and launched a donation campaign of "Dedicate Your Love to Stricken School". Up to now, over one million yuan donation has been received from all walks of life. </seg>
</p>
